==English==

===Etymology===
Old English ''dēaf''.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /dɛf/
====Homophones====
*[[def]]


===Adjective===
'''deaf''' ''or'' '''Deaf''' depending on the meaning; see the definitions below.
<!--the comparative and superlative have been added to the definitions: see below-->
#('''deaf'''; {{compare}} [[deafer]], {{super}} [[deafest]]) Not having the faculty of [[hearing]], or only partially able to hear.
#('''Deaf'''; {{notcomp}}) When capitalized, of or relating to the culture surrounding deaf users of sign language.

